@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Triangwa" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  The game board consists of an 8 by 8 spaces area where some tiles
that have triangular shapes are randomly placed. Some of the
triangular shapes are right triangles, while other are two
triangles placed face to face and have 'hourglasses' shapes.

  To play, click on a tile, if it is empty, that tile will reveal
one or two triangular shapes. However, if the clicked tile is
already occupied by one or two triangular shapes, one of the
following situations can happen:

-Two neighbouring tiles can exchange their positions; for this to
 happen, only one tile (it can be empty or occupied by one or two
 triangles) must be next, either horizontally or vertically to the
 clicked tile. The other neighbouring positions must be 3 empty
 spaces, or one or more of the game board's borders.

-A tile can move by one position; in that case, if there are 3
 neighbouring tiles next, horizontally and vertically (or one or
 more of the game board's borders), as well as an empty space. By
 clicking on the tile, it will move toward the empty space.

  When tiles that contain triangles have contiguous sides that are
parallel to those of the triangles of neighbouring tiles, these
tiles are then eliminated and you get points according to the
number of removed tiles. 2 eliminated tiles give 1 point, 3
eliminated tiles give 5 points.

  After a move is made, whatever the result, a new tile will appear
on the game board. Continue the game until the board is either
completely empty or full. In both cases, the game ends. If the
board is empty, your final score will be doubled...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

